sentence: The PowerShares Dynamic Software Portfolio ETF ( PSJ ) is seeing unusually high volume in afternoon trading Tuesday, with over 251,000 shares traded versus three month average volume of about 25,000.
Shares of PSJ were down about 1.1% on the day.

Components of that ETF with the highest volume on Tuesday were Salesforce.com ( CRM ), trading up about 4.3% with over 11.3 million shares changing hands so far this session, and Activision Blizzard ( ATVI ), off about 0.3% on volume of over 8.5 million shares.

Sabre ( SABR ) is the component faring the best Tuesday, higher by about 4.3% on the day, while Paycom Software ( PAYC ) is lagging other components of the PowerShares Dynamic Software Portfolio ETF, trading lower by about 5.9%.
